reviewText: The Wiggles just love to have fun, every day, inside Playhouse Disney...now, three seperate episodes of The Wiggles are put together to become one big music video movie called, Wiggly Play Time.As always, Greg's my favorite and I love the way he's the Magician King in The Wiggles World.The (episode names) are, History, Family, and Play.
summary: Three Wiggles Episodes From Playhouse Disney.
Title: N/A

reviewText: I didn't, and I was very disappointed.  With four showings daily on the Disney Channel, why on earth would I waste my money on a tape full of TV episodes?Besides, the other Wiggles videos offer something different than the formula of the TV show, and that helps maintain my 22-month-old daughter's interest when she watches them.  Not so here.  She's not old enough to really understand viewing a TV show vs. a video, and when I put this one on, she keeps pointing to the cover, assuming I've not yet started the tape.Yes, the box says waaaaay down in the description that this material was culled from TV material, if you read that far.  But if you're like me, you see the shiny box with smiling Wiggles faces, trust the franchise, and buy it.  Oops.If you're looking for TV show material, you'll love it.  Otherwise, buyer beware!  I feel ripped off, which is something I don't often say in reference to The Wiggles.
summary: Know going in that you're just buying TV episodes
Title: N/A

reviewText: My baby, my husband, and I all love The Wiggles! We have all their videos including Dance Party and love them all. I bought this one knowing it contained all the same songs, but thinking it would have fun material to watch. It does not! Through half the tape Murray and Jeff are laying down on fake grass looking up at fake clouds making comments about what they see. Boring! The other skits are equally boring: Anthony- with a horrible orange tan- eating banannas, all of The Wiggles looking for the bunny in the hat, and The Wiggles dressed as cavemen entering a door. That's it, with 13 of the same songs on Toot Toot! and Wiggle Time spliced into the film at very odd intervals. The songs do not coincide with the skits whatsoever, just all of a sudden they show a song out of the blue! Most are right off of the other tapes, but a few are from a Live Wiggles Show. The new songs are worse since no children are present in the live show at all! My baby loves to see the Wiggles dance and move around, not just lay on the grass or stand around! Even the wonderful dancer Dorothy the Dinosaur just stands around in her garden. A few pirates do back flips is all, but no dancing! This tape is a major disapointment! Go buy Dance Party instead! I gave that one 4 much deserves stars. This one can not get more then a 1 star vote from me or my baby!

reviewText: Here we get a sneak peek at the Wiggles t.v. show-and what a great show it is!!  All our faves are here and they all get their time to shine!!  There is still plenty of music to keep the kids entertained and dancing.  The lessons are well done and not too long.  They teach are kids about family and the universe and sun all in a seamless and fun way.  It's a great addition to the Wiggles collection.
Title: N/A

reviewText: Though this is more sedate and not as original (song-wise) as previous Wiggles videos, I'd still highly recommend it.  My two-year-old really likes watching the guys do their numerous silly skits just as much as he enjoys dancing along to the catchy tunes (even I still get a chuckle out of "John Bradlelum"). If your child is into the Wiggles no matter what they're doing, then this one's a good choice.

reviewText: Hour long toddler flypaper featuring four effeminate Aussies, modern dance routines tacked to folk music, a manic pirate with a feather for a sword, and an odd melange of life size talking dogs, octopi, and dinosaurs who grow roses. In other words, your kid will love it.
